<br>
In this story, your were authorized to kill, under the seal of King Thex.  That is not murder.  <br>
<br>
The High Elves and all of Norrath had become too comfortable with the status quo.  They knew I was was going to disrupt their stability.  They wanted you to stop me.  To to so, they needed me dead before I handed the egg to Lord Nagafen.<br>
<br>
You were well aware that they wanted me dead, and you knew exactly what I was doing.  And you wanted it to happen.  So you accepted the contract, knowing that they would have sent some other assassin after me who would have prevented the egg transaction.  So you fulfilled the contract, to the letter, and in heterodoxic form, you did that which I was trying to do:  give the egg to Lord Nags.<br>
<br>
My orthodxy was that of the dragons, being a worshipper of Veeshan.  Hence the phrase, &quot;Orthodoxy is my doxy, heterodoxy is thy doxy,&quot;<br>
<br>
Doxy is greek for a position or an opinion.  Ortho is greek <br>
correct.  Hetero is Greek for different.  Heterosexual, othorpoedics, both bear present day translations.<br>
<br>
Heterodoxy is your doxy.  You are a heretic.  You will always be swimming against the tide.  You killed me, thereby fufilling the contract -- and preventing another assassin from being hired -- yet also betrayed your contractees by doing exactly what they wanted to prevent:  giving the dragon egg to Lord Nags.  <br>
<br>
The green stone you stowed in my pack was one of your necromancer soul stones, with your soul in it.  I was to be resurrected with it.  <br>
